FTSE 100 Index Resumes Its Decline After Rising in Early Trading in London

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-28T07:26:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/ftse-100-index-resumes-its-decline-after-rising-in-early-trading-in-london.html
U.K. stocks resumed a decline after
briefly erasing losses. The FTSE 100 Index fell 0.5 percent to
5,270.3 at 8:24 a.m. in  London , snapping a three-day rally for
the benchmark gauge. The gauge lost 1.1 percent at the open.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
